ast. Held once every 19 days, the Feast is the local community&#039;s regular worship gathering that promotes and sustains the unity of the local Baha&#039;i community.</p><p>For more information, please e-mail Nadia: nadia@labahais.org</p>">Details</a></div><div class="activitylisttitle">Nineteen Day Feast <br />(Daytime)</div><div class="activitylistdate">Thu Apr 9 2:00PM</div><div class="activitylistdetails"><a id="nadia@labahais.org-2015-04-09-14:00-Nineteen-Day-Feast-(Daytime)" tabindex="0" class="btn btn-blue btn-sm" data-toggle="popover" data-trigger="focus" title="Details" data-html="true" data-content="<p>The centerpiece of Baha&#039;i community life is the Nineteen Day Feast. Held once every 19 days, the Feast is the local community&#039;s regular worship gathering that promotes and sustains the unity of the local Baha&#039;i community.</p><p>For more information, please e-mail Nadia: nadia@labahais.org</p>">Details</a></div><div class="activitylisttitle">Fireside Discussion <br />(in Spanish)</div><div class="activitylistdate">Fri Apr 10 7:30PM</div><div class="activitylistdetails"><a id="nadia@labahais.org-2015-04-10-19:30-Fireside-Discussion-(in-Spanish)" tabindex="0" class="btn btn-blue btn-sm" data-toggle="popover" data-trigger="focus" title="Details" data-html="true" data-content="<p>Informal gathering where short talks and discussions about the Baha&#039;i  Faith are shared in a warm and hospitable atmosphere.</p><p>For more information, please e-mail Nadia: nadia@labahais.org</p>">Details</a></div><div class="activitylisttitle">Muzicality</div><div class="activitylistdate">Sun Apr 12 6:30PM</div><div class="activitylistdetails"><a id="nadia@labahais.org-2015-04-12-18:30-Muzicality" tabindex="0" class="btn btn-blue btn-sm" data-toggle="popover" data-trigger="focus" title="Details" data-html="true" data-content="<p>An open-mic night where people take the stage to share their talents.</p><p>For more information, please e-mail Nadia: nadia@labahais.org</p>">Details</a></div><div class="activitylisttitle">Featured Event:<br /> Annual Election</div><div class="activitylistdate">Mon Apr 20 7:00PM</div><div class="activitylistdetails"><a id="nadia@labahais.org-2015-04-20-19:00-Featured-Event:-Annual-Election" tabindex="0" class="btn btn-blue btn-sm" data-toggle="popover" data-trigger="focus" title="Details" data-html="true" data-content="<p>The Spiritual Assembly of the Baha&#039;is of Los Angeles announces the Annual Meeting of the Los Angeles Baha&#039;i Community on Monday evening, April 20th, 2015, for the election of the Spiritual Assembly for the coming year and for annual reports and consultation.  The annual election and meeting will begin promptly at 7:00 p.m.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Voting List and Ballot: A current voting list for the Los Angeles Baha&#039;i Community will be posted at the election. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Absentee Votes: If you cannot attend the election in person due to travel plans, extended illness or some other reason, please send your ballot in time to be received on or before April 20th.  The absentee vote will be accepted only if it arrives before the election.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Instructions for Mailing or Sending in Your Ballot:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;1. Fill out your ballot by printing on it nine different names of members of the Los Angeles Baha&#039;i Community.  Ballots with more than or fewer than nine names (or a name repeated) will not be eligible.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;2. Place the completed ballot in the enclosed envelope marked &quot;Ballot,&quot; or in an unmarked envelope.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;3. Insert the envelope containing your ballot in the envelope marked &quot;Ballot Envelop Enclosed.&quot; Your full name, address and Baha&#039;i ID must be on this envelope for your votes to be counted.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Baha&#039;i Identification: Current Baha&#039;i credentials will be required of all members attending the meeting.</p><p>For more information, please e-mail Nadia: nadia@labahais.org</p>">Details</a></div><div class="activitylisttitle">Featured Event:<br /> Celebrating the First Day of Ridvan</div><div class="activitylistdate">Tue Apr 21 3:00PM</div><div class="activitylistdetails"><a id="nadia@labahais.org-2015-04-21-15:00-Featured-Event:-Celebrating-the-First-Day-of-Ridvan" tabindex="0" class="btn btn-blue btn-sm" data-toggle="popover" data-trigger="focus" title="Details" data-html="true" data-content="<p>The annual Baha&#039;i festival commemorates the 12 days (April 21-May 2, 1863) when Baha&#039;u&#039;llah, the founder of the Baha&#039;i Faith, resided in a garden called Ridvan (Paradise) in Baghdad, Iraq. At this time He publicly proclaimed His mission as God&#039;s messenger for this age. The first (April 21), ninth (April 29) and twelfth (May 2) days are celebrated as holy days when work is suspended.</p><p>For more information, please e-mail Nadia: nadia@labahais.org</p>">Details</a></div><div class="activitylisttitle">Collective Nineteen Day Feast of Jamal <br />(Beauty)</div><div class="activitylistdate">Mon Apr 27 8:00PM</div><div class="activitylistdetails"><a id="nadia@labahais.org-2015-04-27-20:00-Collective-Nineteen-Day-Feast-of-Jamal-(Beauty)" tabindex="0" class="btn btn-blue btn-sm" data-toggle="popover" data-trigger="focus" title="Details" data-html="true" data-content="<p></p><p>For more information, please e-mail Nadia: nadia@labahais.org</p>">Details</a></div><div class="activitylisttitle">Celebrating the Ninth Day of Ridvan</div><div class="activitylistdate">Tue Apr 28 8:30PM</div><div class="activitylistdetails"><a id="nadia@labahais.org-2015-04-28-20:30-Celebrating-the-Ninth-Day-of-Ridvan" tabindex="0" class="btn btn-blue btn-sm" data-toggle="popover" data-trigger="focus" title="Details" data-html="true" data-content="<p>The annual Baha&#039;i festival commemorates the 12 days (April 21-May 2, 1863) when Baha&#039;u&#039;llah, the founder of the Baha&#039;i Faith, resided in a garden called Ridvan (Paradise) in Baghdad, Iraq. At this time He publicly proclaimed His mission as God&#039;s messenger for this age. The first (April 21), ninth (April 29) and twelfth (May 2) days are celebrated as holy days when work is suspended.</p><p>For more information, please e-mail Nadia: nadia@labahais.org</p>">Details</a></div><div class="activitylisttitle">Celebrating the Twelfth Day of Ridvan</div><div class="activitylistdate">Fri May 1 12:00AM</div><div class="activitylistdetails"><a id="nadia@labahais.org-2015-05-01-00:00-Celebrating-the-Twelfth-Day-of-Ridvan" tabindex="0" class="btn btn-blue btn-sm" data-toggle="popover" data-trigger="focus" title="Details" data-html="true" data-content="<p>The annual Baha&#039;i festival commemorates the 12 days (April 21-May 2, 1863) when Baha&#039;u&#039;llah, the founder of the Baha&#039;i Faith, resided in a garden called Ridvan (Paradise) in Baghdad, Iraq. At this time He publicly proclaimed His mission as God&#039;s messenger for this age. The first (April 21), ninth (April 29) and twelfth (May 2) days are celebrated as holy days when work is suspended.</p><p>For more information, please e-mail Nadia: nadia@labahais.org</p>">Details</a></div></div><div class="text-left popoverex activitylistneighborhoodgroups"><div class='activitylistneighborhood'>Marina del Rey</div><div class="activitylisttitle">Devotional at the Beach</div><div class="activitylistdate">Sat Apr 4 6:30PM</div><div class="activitylistdetails"><a id="ladan@labahais.org-2015-04-04-18:30-Devotional-at-the-Beach" tabindex="0" class="btn btn-blue btn-sm" data-toggle="popover" data-trigger="focus" title="Details" data-html="true" data-content="<p>A space to get together every week and pray</p><p>For more information, please e-mail Ladan: ladan@labahais.org</p>">Details</a></div></div><div class="text-left popoverex activitylistneighborhoodgroups"><div class='activitylistneighborhood'>Martin Luther King Jr / Western</div><div class="activitylisttitle">Devo